    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-29T08:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-29T08:30:00-05:00" n="287"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">648T.006/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Nairobi</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bailey</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nairobi</hi>
                        </placeName> [, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-29T16:00:00+02:30"
                            >November 29, 1939—4 p.m.</date>]<lb/>[Received 10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Effective November 15, permit required to import articles into Kenya, Tanganyika,
                    Uganda. Permit also necessary to buy foreign exchange.</p>
                <p>Copy decree airmailed today.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bailey</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
